==English==
===Etymology===
From Icelandic, [[Ása]] (genitive of [[Áss]], meaning "[[good]] [[gods]]" or "[[Æsir]]") + [[Trú]] (meaning "[[belief]]" or "[[religion]]").
===Alternative Spelling===
*When diacritic characters are unavailable, this word may be spellt ''[[Asatru]]'''
===Proper Noun===
'''Ásatrú''' (no plural)
#belief in and worship of the [[Æsir]]
#a [[faith]], based on this belief and worship, which seeks to reconstruct and practise the old [[Norse]], [[Germanic]], and [[Anglo-Saxo-Jutic]] [[heathen]] religion(s).

----------
==Icelandic==
===Etymology===
[[Ása]], genitive of [[Áss]], + [[Trú]].
===Proper Noun===
'''Ásatrú''' (no plural)
#an officially recognised Icelandic religion based upon belief in and worship of the [[Æsir]], which seeks to reconstruct and practise the old [[Norse]][[heathen]] religion.

